All models are trained with the similar settings: a base learning rate of \(10^{-4}\) per 256 batch size, an AdamW optimizer with \(_{1}=0.9\), \(_{2}=0.95\), decay \(=0.05\), a batch size from 768 to 1024 and training epochs from 200 to 350 (depends on model size). The evaluations in Sec. 5 suggest that such a simple model design are capable of scaling and generalizing well.

